<section class="section3">
  <h2 class="section3-heading">Why vCruit and online video can improve results . . . </h2>
	
  <div class="section3-block">
    <h2>Video gets more people's attention</h2>
  	<p class="lead"><i class="icon-stop"></i>Click rates for email campaigns increased by more than 300% when the email included a video. ~ Wistia</p>
  </div>
  
	<div class="section3-block">
    <h2>Video keeps more people's attention</h2>
  	<p class="lead"><i class="icon-stop"></i>Buyers are 98% more likely to watch a presentation on video than to listen to a sales rep. ~ Forrester Research</p>
  </div>
  
	<div class="section3-block">
    <h2>Video boosts social media engagement</h2>
  	<p class="lead"><i class="icon-stop"></i>People are most likely to engage with branded content on social media that contains pictures (44%) and videos (37%). ~ Performics</p>
  </div>
  
	<div class="section3-block">
    <h2>Video helps to build familiarity</h2>
  	<p class="lead"><i class="icon-stop"></i>Seeing someone's eyes and hearing their voice goes a long way.</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="section3-block">  
    <h2>Video saves you time and improves efficiency</h2>
  	<p class="lead"><i class="icon-stop"></i>Say it once for everyone to hear and quickly identify those who are interested.</p>
  </div>
</section>

